## PHP-FPM Tuning
```ini
; docker/php/php-fpm.conf
[www]
pm = dynamic
pm.max_children = 20
pm.start_servers = 5
pm.min_spare_servers = 3
pm.max_spare_servers = 8
pm.max_requests = 500
request_terminate_timeout = 60s
```

```ini
; docker/php/opcache.ini
opcache.enable=1
opcache.memory_consumption=256
opcache.max_accelerated_files=10000
opcache.revalidate_freq=0
opcache.validate_timestamps=0   ; set to 1 in dev
opcache.fast_shutdown=1
```

## MySQL Tuning
```yaml
db:
  image: mysql:8.0
  command: >
    --innodb-buffer-pool-size=512M
    --innodb-log-file-size=128M
    --max-connections=150
    --slow-query-log=1
    --long-query-time=1
  volumes:
    - db_data:/var/lib/mysql    # NEVER bind mount DB data
  mem_limit: 1g
```

## Nginx Inside Docker
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    root /var/www/html/public;

    gzip on;
    gzip_types text/plain text/css application/json application/javascript;

    location ~* \.(js|css|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|svg|woff2)$ {
        expires 1y;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
        try_files $uri =404;
    }

    location ~ \.php$ {
        fastcgi_pass app:9000;
        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $realpath_root$fastcgi_script_name;
        include fastcgi_params;
        fastcgi_read_timeout 60;
        fastcgi_buffer_size 16k;
        fastcgi_buffers 4 16k;
    }

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
    }
}
```

## Resource Limits — Always Set
```yaml
services:
  web:
    mem_limit: 512m
    mem_reservation: 256m
    cpus: '1.0'
  api:
    mem_limit: 1g
    mem_reservation: 512m
    cpus: '2.0'
  db:
    mem_limit: 1g
  redis:
    mem_limit: 256m
    command: redis-server --maxmemory 200mb --maxmemory-policy allkeys-lru
```

## Health Checks — Always Add
```yaml
services:
  api:
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD", "curl", "-f", "http://localhost/health"]
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3
      start_period: 40s
  db:
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD", "mysqladmin", "ping", "-h", "localhost"]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5
```

## Dev vs Production Split
```
docker-compose.yml          # base — shared config
docker-compose.dev.yml      # bind mounts, ports, watch mode
docker-compose.prod.yml     # resource limits, restart: always
```

```bash
# Dev
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.dev.yml up

# Production
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
```

## Diagnostic Commands
```bash
docker stats                                          # live resource usage
docker compose logs -f --tail=50 <service>            # follow logs
docker image history <image>                          # layer size breakdown
docker system df                                      # disk usage
docker compose build --no-cache <service>             # force clean rebuild
docker exec -it <db> mysql -u root -p -e "SHOW PROCESSLIST;"
docker exec -it <container> df -h                     # disk inside container
```

## What I Always Flag
- Bind mounting node_modules or vendor from host → severe slowdown
- Missing .dockerignore on every service → bloated build context
- COPY . . before npm install → broken layer caching
- No resource limits → one service starves all others
- Bind mounting database data directory → corruption risk
- Using `latest` tag in production → unpredictable deployments
- Running as root inside container → security risk
- No health checks → race conditions on startup
- PHP memory_limit below 256M for Laravel → OOM crashes under load
